v0.28

  - Fix tests for 5.26
Skip coverage on 5.8

Skip pod link check on travis

it doesn't like our own `L<text-vimcolor>`
Fix tests for 5.26

v0.27

   Fix installer for 5.24.1+
Fix installer for 5.24.1+

v0.26

  - Fix test failures for vim 6.
  - Use Test::File::ShareDir to simplify testing.

Rewrite groups test to work with vim 6

() => Delimeter on vim 7
() => Operator  on vim 6
Hack status badges into the readme
Restore geoffr's copyright in readme.mkdn
Setup minimal travis configuration

Fix module load order in test

The test mod needs to be loaded before the actual mod,
but if the test mod is loaded we don't even need to explicitly load
the real mod.

Use Test::File::ShareDir instead of symlink hack

Simpler and more consistent.
Enables prove -l to work even without the symlink (like in a build).
Add new dist_file to share dir test
Declare XML::Parser as DevelopRequires for tests

v0.25

  - Add 'all_syntax_groups' option to enable additional syntax groups
    instead of just the primary ones.  Thanks Hinrik rn Sigursson!
Commit LICENSE file to repo so dzil will save it
Add all-syntax-groups to Changes and thank Hinrik

Don't print GEOFFR's copyright twice

Now that ReadmeAnyFromPod is on release, this was too much.

Tell dzil to treat various t/ files as binary

Perl::MinimumVersion was barfing on the ANSI file
and detecting 5.012 from t/.vim.

Refactor package variable definitions

* Reduce duplication of syntax group names
* Don't include ansi colors ("red") in SYNTAX_TYPE
Test syntax and ansi color package variables
Add --all-syntax-groups option to bin script

Support all of Vim's syntax groups

This allows for much more detailed highlighting.

This implementation is a general solution to a hack we've been
using in the vim-perl test suite.

v0.24

  - Simplify encoding tests and mark a few as TODO
    while the library undergoes some refactoring.
Change generated root README from pod to markdown
